\nwell with those in the fits without including the momentum-dependence of the\n$\\rho-\\omega$ mixing within errors. In addition, based on the fitted values of\nthe involved parameters, we find that in the decay width of $\\omega \\rightarrow\n\\pi^+\\pi^-$ the contribution from the direct $\\omega_I\\pi\\pi$ coupling is\ncomparable with the contribution due to the $\\rho-\\omega$ mixing.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 29 May 2022 13:27:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 1 Jun 2022 04:34:21 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 13 Mar 2023 12:46:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-14"}
